===============================================================================
Salty Files               

www.thomasmueller.ch              
===============================================================================

-------------------------------------------------------------------------------
	General
-------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Salty Files is based on Java (JDK 1.4.2)

Used libraries:
	Runtime:
		ant-1.6.1 (http://ant.apache.org)
		log4j-1.2.8.jar (http://logging.apache.org)
		forms-1.0.4.jar and looks-1.2.1.jar (http://www.jgoodies.com)
	Testsing:
		junit.jar (http://www.junit.org)

OS Support:
	Linux, 
	Windows 2000, 
	Windows XP

This software provides a user interface to encryt or decrypt files (text or binary) 
on the file system.

Features: 
	Encyption/decryption (Algorithm: PBE-WithMD5AndDES), 
	file compression (zip), 
	user interface 
	
-------------------------------------------------------------------------------
	Installation
-------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Preconditions:

You must install Java JRE 1.4.2 or later to run the program.

Developers must install Java SDK 1.4.2 or later to run and compile the program.

You may download it directly from:

	http://java.sun.com/j2se/1.4.2/download.html
	
You can test your installation of the Java Runtime Environment (JRE) by typing:

	java -version 

in a command window. A message similar to the one below shoud appear:
	
	java version "1.4.2"
	Java(TM) 2 Runtime Environment, Standard Edition (build 1.4.2-b28)
	Java HotSpot(TM) Client VM (build 1.4.2-b28, mixed mode)

Your done.	


-------------------------------------------------------------------------------
	Configuration
-------------------------------------------------------------------------------
No configuration is needed to run the program, but you may change the 
configuration of the log-system by changing the entries in the properties file 
log4j.properties.

-------------------------------------------------------------------------------
	How to Start the Application
-------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Open a command window and change to the directory wheres this README-file is 
located

Type:

	java -jar saltyfiles.jar 

